ANTHRAX, HUMAN, LIVESTOCK - GHANA (03): (UPPER EAST)
****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 25 Apr 2012
Source: Joy News/Ghana, myjoyonline [edited]
http://edition.myjoyonline.com/pages/news/201204/85499.php


Anthrax kills 2 persons and 20 cows in Bawku
--------------------------------------------
An outbreak of anthrax, a deadly infectious disease has killed 2 persons and 20 cows in Gogo, a farming community in the Bawku West District of the Upper East Region. The victims, both males, are said to have handled the carcasses of affected cattle, according to veterinary officials in the area. Another 2 people have been admitted at the hospital for suspected anthrax symptoms.

In an interview with Myjoyonline, the DCE [district chief executive] for Bawku West, Hon. Moro Adam Anabah said the situation is under control adding that veterinary officials have moved to quarantine and vaccinate the animals in the area. He said the 20 dead cows have been buried and affected ones are vaccinated to prevent a major outbreak in the area.

The Bawku West district chief executive hinted that, there is a temporary ban on slaughtering and movement of animals in the area. He further hinted that several measures have been put in place to ensure that there is no outbreak of anthrax in the district.

He however suspected that the infectious disease might have infiltrated from Burkina Faso since the affected area shares a boundary with that country. The DCE said there will be security patrols on the borders to prevent movement of animals [into] the country. He therefore advised the people in the area to report any suspected symptoms of anthrax to the nearest clinic or the district assembly.

[byline: Hamza Lansah Lolly]

